          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Gradual over 3‚Äì6 months</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-4 border-l-4 border-purple-500">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 text-sm mb-1">Full Recovery</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Most patients at 6‚Äì12 months</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-amber-800 text-sm mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span>‚ö†Ô∏è</span> What to Expect
        </h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-2">
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="text-amber-600">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span><strong>Nerve healing is slow</strong> ‚Äì Recovery depends on nerve regeneration (approximately <strong>1mm per day</strong>). Full recovery can continue for up to 12 months</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="text-amber-600">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span><strong>Atrophy may be partially irreversible</strong> ‚Äì Some muscle wasting from long-standing compression may not fully recover, but function typically improves significantly</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-2">
            <span class="text-amber-600">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span><strong>Patience is key</strong> ‚Äì Rushing rehabilitation can lead to setbacks. Follow the phases carefully</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Immediate Post-Surgery (Days 0-3)</h3>
      
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-bold shrink-0">‚úì</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-slate-800">Sling Use</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Wear sling for comfort during first 3-10 days (typically 1-2 weeks). Remove for exercises and when resting. Since no tendon was repaired, protection is less strict than rotator cuff surgery.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-bold shrink-0">‚úì</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-slate-800">Ice Application</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Apply ice 15-20 minutes, 3-4 times daily to reduce swelling. Protect skin with cloth.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-emerald-600 font-bold shrink-0">‚úì</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-slate-800">Pain Management</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Take prescribed pain medication as directed. Some discomfort is normal but severe pain should be reported.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="text-rose-600 font-bold shrink-0">‚ö†</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-slate-800">Contact Your Doctor If:</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Fever >38¬∞C, increasing pain/swelling, numbness/tingling in hand, or wound concerns.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Phase Overview -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 text-center">Rehabilitation Phases</h2>
      
