  </section>

  <!-- Phase 1 -->
  <section class="bg-white py-8 border-t border-slate-200">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700 flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold">
          1
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Phase 1: Protection & Early Motion</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Weeks 0‚Äì4 Post-Surgery</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-emerald-800 mb-2">Goals</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Protect surgical site and allow initial healing</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Reduce pain and inflammation</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Prevent shoulder stiffness</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Maintain elbow/wrist/hand motion</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Begin gentle passive range of motion (ROM)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Exercises - Phase 1</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-4">
        <em>Based on Rothman Orthopaedics and Denver Shoulder Surgeon protocols.</em> All exercises should be pain-free or minimal discomfort only.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        
        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">1. Pendulum Exercises (Days 1-7)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Lean forward, support yourself with your good arm on a table. Let the operated arm hang freely and gently swing it:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Forward and backward (10 swings)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Side to side (10 swings)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Small circles clockwise and counterclockwise (10 each direction)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 3-4 times daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">2. Passive Range of Motion - Flexion (Week 1-4)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Lie on your back. Use your good arm or a stick/wand to gently lift your operated arm overhead.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Start with 90¬∞ (arm straight up)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Progress to 120-150¬∞ by week 4</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Hold for 5-10 seconds</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 10 repetitions, 2-3 times daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">3. Passive External Rotation (Week 2-4)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Lie on your back with elbow at 90¬∞. Use your good hand or a stick to gently rotate your arm outward.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Start gently, to tolerance</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Progress to 30-45¬∞ external rotation</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Do NOT force into pain</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 10 repetitions, 2-3 times daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">4. Scapular Sets (Week 1-4)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Sit with good posture. Gently squeeze shoulder blades together and down toward back pockets. Prevents hunching forward.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 10 repetitions holding 5 seconds, 2-3 times daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">5. Elbow/Wrist/Hand Motion</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Keep your elbow, wrist, and hand mobile to prevent stiffness.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Elbow flexion/extension (10 reps)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Wrist circles (10 each direction)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Finger flexion/extension (10 reps)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> Multiple times daily</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-rose-800 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span>üö´</span> Precautions - Phase 1
        </h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
          <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>No cross-body stretch</strong> ‚Äì Avoid pulling arm across chest (puts tension on healing nerve)</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ No active lifting of the arm (wait until Phase 2)</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ No resistance exercises</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ No reaching behind back</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ No heavy lifting or pushing</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Avoid sleeping on the operated shoulder</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-sky-50 border border-sky-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-sky-800 mb-2">Progress to Phase 2 When:</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
          <li>‚úì Minimal pain at rest</li>
          <li>‚úì Passive ROM at least 120¬∞ flexion, 30¬∞ external rotation</li>
          <li>‚úì Cleared by your physiotherapist or surgeon (typically week 4)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Phase 2 -->
  <section class="bg-slate-50 py-8 border-t border-slate-200">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-sky-100 text-sky-700 flex items-center justify-center text-xl font-bold">
          2
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Phase 2: Active ROM & Light Strengthening</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Weeks 4‚Äì8 Post-Surgery</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-sky-50 border border-sky-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-sky-800 mb-2">Goals</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Achieve full passive ROM</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Begin active ROM without pain</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Start gentle isometric strengthening</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Improve scapular control</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Gradually restore daily function</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Exercises - Phase 2</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mb-4">
        <em>Continue passive ROM from Phase 1, add active exercises as tolerated.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        
        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">1. Active-Assisted Flexion & Wall Slide (Week 4-6)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            <strong>Method 1:</strong> Use your good arm or cane/stick to assist lifting the operated arm overhead.<br/>
            <strong>Method 2 (Wall Slide):</strong> Stand facing wall, place towel under hand, slide hand up wall as high as comfortable without shrugging shoulder.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Gradually reduce assistance as strength improves</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Progress to full active flexion by week 8</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 10-15 repetitions, 2-3 times daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">2. Active External Rotation (Week 5-8)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Stand with elbow at side, bent to 90¬∞. Slowly rotate arm outward (away from body). This exercise is critical for infraspinatus recovery.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Start without resistance</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Progress slowly ‚Äì this muscle has been weak</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 10-15 repetitions, 2-3 times daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">3. Isometric Exercises - "The Statue" (Week 6-8)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Gentle muscle activation without moving the joint. Push against a wall with 25% effort ‚Äì like a statue holding position.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>External rotation:</strong> Stand with back of hand against wall, elbow at 90¬∞. Gently press outward (hold 5 sec)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Abduction:</strong> Stand with outside of elbow against wall. Press outward (hold 5 sec)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Flexion:</strong> Push forward against wall with palm (hold 5 sec)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 10 repetitions each, once daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">4. Supine Active Punch - Serratus Activation (Week 6-8)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Lie on your back with arm pointing to ceiling, elbow straight. "Punch" fist higher by lifting shoulder blade off surface. Lower slowly.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 2 sets of 10 repetitions, daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">4. Scapular Retraction (Week 4-8)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Sitting or standing, squeeze shoulder blades together. Hold for 5 seconds.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 10-15 repetitions, 2 times daily</p>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span>‚ö†Ô∏è</span> Precautions - Phase 2
        </h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
          <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Continued caution with cross-body stretching</strong></li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ No heavy lifting (>2kg / 5 lbs)</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ No forceful overhead activities</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Stop if sharp pain occurs</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Progress gradually ‚Äì nerve healing takes time</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-sky-50 border border-sky-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-sky-800 mb-2">Progress to Phase 3 When:</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
          <li>‚úì Full passive ROM achieved</li>
          <li>‚úì Active ROM at least 140¬∞ flexion, 40¬∞ external rotation</li>
          <li>‚úì Minimal pain with daily activities</li>
          <li>‚úì Typically around week 8</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Phase 3 -->
  <section class="bg-white py-8 border-t border-slate-200">
