        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Phase 3: Progressive Strengthening</h2>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Weeks 8‚Äì12 Post-Surgery</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">Goals</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm text-slate-700 space-y-1">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Restore full active ROM</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Progressive strengthening of rotator cuff</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Improve shoulder stability and endurance</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Normalize scapular mechanics</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Return to light functional activities</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Exercises - Phase 3</h3>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        
        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">1. Resistance Band - External Rotation</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Stand with elbow at side, bent 90¬∞. Hold resistance band and rotate arm outward against resistance.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ Start with light resistance (yellow/red Theraband)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Critical for infraspinatus recovery</strong></li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Progress resistance as strength improves</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2"><strong>Frequency:</strong> 2-3 sets of 15 repetitions, daily</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">2. "Full Can" Exercise - Supraspinatus (Week 8-12)</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 mb-2">
            Stand holding light weight (1-2 lbs). Lift arm out to side and slightly forward (30¬∞ angle), <strong>thumb pointing UP</strong> (like holding a full can). Lift only to shoulder height.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ <strong>Important:</strong> Do NOT turn thumb down ("Empty Can") ‚Äì this stresses the healing area</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Slow, controlled motion</li>
          </ul>
